.SH NAME
HTMLImageElement.src \- HTMLImageElement: src property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]HTMLImageElement\f[R] property \f[B]\f[CB]src\f[B]\f[R], which
reflects the HTML \f[CR]src\f[R] attribute, specifies the image to
display in the \f[CR]<img>\f[R] element.
.SH VALUE
When providing only a single image, rather than a set of images from
which the browser selects the best match for the viewport size and
display pixel density, the \f[CR]src\f[R] attribute is a string
specifying the URL of the desired image.
This can be set either within the HTML itself using the \f[CR]src\f[R]
content attribute, or programmatically by setting the element\[cq]s
\f[CR]src\f[R] property.
.PP
If you use the \f[CR]srcset\f[R] content attribute to provide multiple
image options for different display pixel densities, the URL specified
by the \f[CR]src\f[R] attribute is used in one of two ways:
.IP \[bu] 2
as a fallback for browsers that don\[cq]t support \f[CR]srcset\f[R].
.IP \[bu] 2
as an equivalent for specifying an image in \f[CR]srcset\f[R] with the
size multiplier \f[CR]1x\f[R]; that is, the image specified by
\f[CR]src\f[R] is used on low\-density screens (such as typical 72 DPI
or 96 DPI displays).
.PP
Additionally, if you use \f[CR]src\f[R] along with \f[I]both\f[R]
\f[CR]sizes\f[R] (or the corresponding \f[CR]sizes\f[R] content
attribute) \f[I]and\f[R] \f[CR]srcset\f[R] in order to choose an image
based on the viewport size, the \f[CR]src\f[R] attribute is only used as
a fallback for browsers that don\[cq]t support \f[CR]sizes\f[R] and
\f[CR]srcset\f[R]; otherwise, it\[cq]s not used at all.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Specifying a single image
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]img\f[R]
  src=\[dq]grapefruit\-slice\-332\-332.jpg\[dq]
  width=\[dq]160\[dq]
  alt=\[dq]Slices of grapefruit, looking yummy.\[dq] />
.EE
.SS Result
.SS Using src with an image set
When using a set of images with the \f[CR]srcset\f[R] property, the
\f[CR]src\f[R] serves as either a fallback for older browsers, or as the
\f[CR]1x\f[R] size of the image.
.SS HTML
.SS Result
.SS Specifying a fallback for viewport\-based selection
When using viewport\-bases selection of an image from a
\f[CR]srcset\f[R] by also specifying the \f[CR]sizes\f[R] property, the
\f[CR]src\f[R] property serves as the fallback to be used on browsers
that don\[cq]t support viewport\-based selection.
Browsers that \f[I]do\f[R] support viewport\-based selection will ignore
\f[CR]src\f[R] in this situation.
